                        font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;
                        ">
                        <p style="font-family: arial, sans-serif; ">Andres



                          Garcia-Saavedra received his B.Sc. in
                          Telecommunication Engineering from Universidad
                          of Cantabria in 2009, and his M.Sc. in
                          Telematics Engineering from<span
                            class="Apple-converted-space">&nbsp;</span><span
                            style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial,
                            Helvetica, sans-serif; ">Universidad Carlos
                            III de Madrid (UC3M)</span><span
                            style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial,
                            Helvetica, sans-serif; ">&nbsp;in 2010.
                            Currently he&nbsp;</span><span
                            style="font-family: Arial, Helvetica,
                            sans-serif; font-size: 10pt; ">holds the
                            position of Teaching Assistant&nbsp;</span><span
                            style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial,
                            Helvetica, sans-serif; ">and&nbsp;</span><span
                            style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Arial,
                            Helvetica, sans-serif; ">pursues his
                            Ph.D.&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size:
                            10pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica,
                            sans-serif; ">in the Telematics Department
                            of UC3M</span><span style="font-size: 10pt;
                            font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; ">.
                            His work focuses on performance evaluation
                            and energy efficiency of wireless networks.</span></p>
                      </td>
                    </tr>
